<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Costly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Costly,</orth> 1) sumptuous, expensive: <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.341" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 341</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.354" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 354</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.165" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 165</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 258</bibl>. Compar. <cit><quote>--ier,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 78</bibl></cit>. Adverbially: <cit><quote>painting thy outward walls so c. gay,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 146.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 146, 4</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) richly adorned, gorgeous: <cit><quote>how c. summer was at hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 9, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a c. suit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 59.</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>c. thy habit as thy purse can buy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 70</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Cost,</emph> subst. 2).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>